# Implementation Plan: Hide Test User from Directory

The objective is to hide the test Operations Manager user ("Anthony Kimeu") from the public Employees directory while retaining the account in the database for continued testing.

## Proposed Changes

### [Database & Backend]

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/prisma/schema.prisma)
- Add an `isTest` boolean field to the `User` model with a default value of `false`.
- This provides a standard way to distinguish test/hidden accounts from production data.

#### [MODIFY] [employee.controller.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/controllers/employee.controller.ts)
- Update the `getAllEmployees` and `employee.count` functions to include a filter for `isTest: false`.
- This ensures that test users are automatically excluded from the Team Directory and employee counts.

### [Data Migration]

#### [SCRIPT] [mark-test-user.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/scripts/mark-test-user.ts) [NEW]
- Create a one-off script to find the user "Anthony Kimeu" and set `isTest: true`.

